      "side": 1,
      "message": "The existing policy is that anything marked deprecated can\u0027t be removed before a tag is made capturing its deprecation. We can remove it at any point following that first tag (there may be subsequent tags too). We can make a tag at any time, i.e. I don\u0027t require any minimum amount of time needs to pass between creating tags. My intent is that they\u0027re just used as \"barriers\" (in the memory-model sense) for removals.",
